  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study was to analyse the independent and joint effects of the components of
      the metabolic syndrome (MetS) on the incidence of diabetes in people with impaired glucose
      tolerance (IGT) and to assess the effect of acarbose by MetS status.

      Double-blind placebo controlled trial, 1,368 patients, follow-up time 3.3 years. MetS by ATP
      III definition with fasting plasma glucose of â‰¥ 6.1 mmol/l as limit for impaired fasting
      glucose (IFG).
    </textblock>
